    <body>
      <section eId="sec_10_1002">
        <num>10-1002</num>
        <heading>Rules and regulations</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_10_1002__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>To protect and preserve the village property and apparatus of the\nfire department.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_10_1002__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>To prevent danger from fires and to protect property exposed to\ndestruction or injury by fire.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_10_1002__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>To provide for pulling down, blowing up and the removal of\nbuildings and property to arrest the progress of fires or extinguish the\nsame.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_10_1002__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>To provide for the installation of yard hydrant systems connected\nwith the public water supply system in accessible locations on private\nproperty for the protection of multiple residences enumerated in the\nmultiple residence law where the possibility of a serious fire hazard is\ndetermined by the board to exist.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
